  BY UMMU ABUBAKAR  A truck laden with Premium Motor Spirit has exploded in Jebba, Moro Local Government Area of Kwara State. No fewer than six persons were killed in the explosion, which occured in the early hours of Wednesday. The petrol tanker was said to have rammed into residential buildings, spilling its content, as the driver lost control. Over 30 houses were said to have been burnt in the explosions that followed. Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq has commiserated with the families of those who lost their lives and properties, describing the incident as devastating and sad. In a statement by his media aide, Rafiu Ajakaye, the Governor expressed regret over the development, “especially with the loss of lives and millions of naira worth of properties and farmlands.” His media aide said, “He (the Governor) sends his heartfelt condolences to the affected families. He urges them to take heart and remain calm as believers. He has also directed the State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA) to quickly move in to determine the material loss. “He also commends the Kwara state Fire Service and other responders for their efforts which helped to curtail the raging inferno and minimise the loss. Once again, he condoles with the victims and their families on this very sad incident, and prays to God Almighty to repose the souls of the deceased.”  